You'll get a bedsore like that.

84
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:26,990
Why are you still...

85
00:10:26,990 --> 00:10:29,050
Hurry up and get ready.

86
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:31,240
The hospital closes at 4.

87
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:35,200
I almost died trying to find a hospital open during the holiday.

88
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,000
Hospital? We're going to the hospital?

89
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,100
Yeah. We need to.

90
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,870
Will you live with panic disorder forever?

91
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,300
Where did my wallet go?

92
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,810
Hey, have you seen my wallet?

93
00:10:52,810 --> 00:10:54,770
Did I leave it in my car?

94
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:09,170
Since when do you not ask questions

95
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:12,070
and just stare at people?

96
00:11:14,020 --> 00:11:16,030
Well, I...

97
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,390
What? Say it.

98
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:24,070
You've just been...

99
00:11:24,070 --> 00:11:26,240
in my house...

100
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:29,730
That's my choice. What else?

101
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:32,010
Anything else you want to know?

102
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:40,380
Hyun Oh.

103
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:42,220
Yeah? Tell me.

104
00:11:44,860 --> 00:11:47,330
I already have a doctor that I see.

105
00:11:47,330 --> 00:11:49,670
You should've told me!

106
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:52,370
I looked up other hospitals for nothing.

107
00:11:52,370 --> 00:11:54,420
Give me the address.

108
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:55,950
Well...

109
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,400
Hey, Sunbae.

110
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:25,250
Really?

111
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:33,570
I have already met and spoken with the Press Director Seo.

112
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,210
Hello.

113
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:54,600
You don't have an appointment today.

114
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,790
I know.

115
00:12:55,790 --> 00:12:59,660
I wanted to talk to the doctor today.

116
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:02,280
Okay. One moment, Hye Ri.

117
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,870
Is something the matter, Hye Ri?

118
00:13:15,950 --> 00:13:17,950
Doctor.

119
00:13:17,950 --> 00:13:21,600
I'm Eun Ho. Ju Eun Ho.

120
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,330
Doctor, have I been coming here

121
00:13:26,330 --> 00:13:28,800
and say that I'm Hye Ri?

122
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:32,850
Yes.

123
00:13:32,850 --> 00:13:34,940
- I...
- Since when?

124
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:37,310
Since when have I been doing that?

125
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:41,360
What state was I in? Was I not like how I am now?

126
00:13:42,350 --> 00:13:44,540
Doctor, I don't remember.

127
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:47,310
I keep falling asleep in a strange place.

128
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:50,610
I meet strangers. My phone keeps disappearing.

129
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:52,730
And sometimes...

130
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,250
Sometimes...

131
00:13:57,320 --> 00:14:00,330
I remember things I don't recognize.

132
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:05,300
I don't know what they are, and I don't look like myself inside those memories.

133
00:14:05,330 --> 00:14:08,550
I read letters I wrote to myself when I was living as Hye Ri.

134
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:11,080
They don't seem like letters I wrote.

135
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:15,430
I can't believe it. I don't remember writing those letters.

136
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,060
Really...

137
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:20,900
I can't think because I don't want to.

138
00:14:22,090 --> 00:14:24,270
Eun Ho.

139
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:26,900
It must have been so confusing for you.

140
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,930
That's natural.

141
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:32,450
Then, could you tell me...

142
00:14:32,450 --> 00:14:35,900
what kind of person Hye Ri is? The one who wrote you letters.

143
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:40,300
If you could tell me what kind of person she is...

144
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,630
Hye Ri...

145
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,860
I mean, Hye Ri...

146
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:07,310
Yes.

147
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:15,830
is my younger sister...

148
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:24,320
who went missing.

149
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:33,400
Hye Ri, listen carefully.

150
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:37,800
From now on, we can't see Mom and Dad again.

151
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:42,670
- Why not? Because of the accident?
- Yes.

152
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:45,370
There was a big accident.

153
00:15:45,370 --> 00:15:46,680
So...

154
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:49,070
Oppa, you have the most money!

155
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:50,860
You should take them!

156
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:53,240
Why are you bringing that up right now?

157
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:55,460
We don't even have a house.

158
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:57,590
Our place is collateral right now.

159
00:15:57,590 --> 00:16:00,260
We're about to be homeless.

160
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,760
We can't take care of them!

161
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:06,550
You used to adore them. Now, you're scared to take them?

162
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:09,190
I'm busy trying to put food in my mouth.

163
00:16:09,190 --> 00:16:13,150
How are we supposed to take care of them?

164
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:14,420
You take care of them.

165
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:16,150
You have the most money!

166
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:19,490
Frankly, you took all of our dad's money.

167
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:23,700
We live like beggars while you flaunt your wealth.

168
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:26,770
Hey! Are you serious right now?

169
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:28,950
You never did anything for Dad.

170
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:31,510
When Dad was dying, you looked the other way!

171
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:33,980
- It's okay, Hye Ri.
- And now...

172
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:36,980
You have me.

173
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,750
How can you yell at me like this?

174
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,900
Dirty.

175
00:16:42,980 --> 00:16:45,300
Don't do that. That's dirty.

176
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:49,900
You don't have parents anymore. You need to take care of yourselves.

177
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,870
Here.

178
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,710
Hey.

179
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:59,870
Blow your nose. Blow.

180
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:01,830
Good. One more time.

181
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:04,060
Good.

182
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:08,450
Who are you?

183
00:17:11,290 --> 00:17:12,970
Grandma?

184
00:17:13,770 --> 00:17:15,560
That's right!

185
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:20,920
You've always been smart. You remember me!

186
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,010
You're Eun Ho, right?

187
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,670
Then, are you Hye Ri?

188
00:17:27,670 --> 00:17:30,080
Yes, I'm Hye Ri.

189
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:33,050
Hye Ri.

190
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:35,780
Do you want to go with grandma?

191
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:38,870
Want to go live with grandma?

192
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:51,770
Unni, you know what? I came in last in class.

193
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:53,530
Hey, you need to study.

194
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,410
You can't do that when you study with a stranger's money.

195
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:58,370
I'm sorry.

196
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:02,700
But Unni, why is Grandma a stranger?

197
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:04,940
She is.

198
00:18:04,940 --> 00:18:07,110
Do you know how complicated the family tree is?

199
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:12,200
She still raised us, so we basically owe her.

200
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,800
Plus, we'll move out. I signed the lease on a place.

201
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,220
You'll live downstairs, and I'll live upstairs.

202
00:18:19,220 --> 00:18:22,270
What are you talking about? Why would we leave?

203
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:25,600
Hye Ri, if we don't leave, will you live here forever?

204
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,840
Yes. Of course.

205
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,780
Grandma will be bored without us.

206
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,570
Listen to me, Ju Hye Ri.

207
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:40,600
No one in this world is generous without wanting something in return.

208
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:44,820
That's not true. Grandma is generous and doesn't expect anything in return.

209
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:47,530
And it's not like she's being generous.

210
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:50,260
She just loves us.

211
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,350
Love? It's just debt.

212
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:58,350
Unni! You're so weird.

213
00:18:58,350 --> 00:19:01,430
I don't understand anything you're saying.

214
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,580
A graduation trip?

215
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:25,100
You should go. You should definitely go to those things.

216
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:28,880
Go on the graduation trip.

217
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:31,160
You have no friends because you don't go to things like that.

218
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,480
I don't want to go.

219
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,440
I really don't.

220
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,050
Why don't you want to go?

221
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,960
I like being home better.

222
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:41,560
I don't have any friends there.

223
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:46,090
You can make friends there.

224
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:49,500
How can you have no friends even as you're graduating college?

225
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,050
Go make some.

226
00:19:51,050 --> 00:19:55,090
That's how you can be helpful when you start working.

227
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:57,800
I told you you need to be independent now.

228
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:01,200
I found a place you can live in, Ju Hye Ri...

229
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,390
But I really-

230
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:05,220
Go.

231
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:07,850
I'll assume you're going.

232
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:09,880
I can send the money to this account, right?

233
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:13,310
But I really don't want to go, Unni.

234
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:15,780
I don't need friends.

235
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,500
I'm not going.

236
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,580
All I need is you, Unni.

237
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:21,270
Ju Hye Ri!

238
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:23,340
How long are you going to be like this?

239
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:25,430
You need to be independent!

240
00:20:25,430 --> 00:20:28,960
Work hard at something! Make connections!

241
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,800
You need to get ready to be a part of society!

242
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:34,730
Stop complaining and go.

243
00:20:34,730 --> 00:20:37,180
Go make friends!

244
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,430
Yes, hello?

245
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:56,680
I'm sorry.

246
00:20:57,490 --> 00:21:00,160
Could you say that again?

247
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,360
Ju Hye Ri is missing.

248
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:05,000
Hey, Eun Ho.

249
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:10,300
Hye Ri hasn't been answering her phone since yesterday.

250
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:12,360
Did something happen?

251
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,380
Hye... Hye Ri...

252
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:29,530
A, a college student who left for a graduation trip,

253
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:32,030
went missing last night.

254
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:53,480
[As of 2/20/2019, the missing person declaration period is over]

255
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:02,600
Grandma.

256
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:07,980
Grandma, are you there?

257
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:17,600
Grandma, you know...

258
00:22:18,820 --> 00:22:23,200
we'll wait for Hye Ri a little longer, as you said.

259
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,810
Grandma.

260
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:39,010
Grandma?

261
00:22:45,660 --> 00:22:47,510
Grandma...

262
00:22:52,770 --> 00:22:54,760
Grandma!

263
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:59,050
Grandma!

264
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,270
Grandma!

265
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:31,830
[3/4/2012: Working in the parking lot will make me so happy]

266
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:40,700
Working here is not possible.

267
00:23:40,730 --> 00:23:43,380
We don't need anyone else.

268
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:44,980
One person is enough.

269
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:49,500
I'm also not allowed to get paid somewhere else.

270
00:23:49,540 --> 00:23:51,510
I already belong to a company.

271
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:55,030
Then why do you want to do this?

272
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:58,040
Can you just let me sit there?

273
00:23:58,850 --> 00:24:01,060
Well...

274
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:05,000
- That'd be difficult.
- My sister really wanted to do this.

275
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:09,320
Though I don't know why.

276
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,220
Sunbae, what?

277
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,250
I want to do the morning radio.

278
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:34,590
I know there's an opening. Plug me there.

279
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:36,800
I can't work at night.

280
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:38,750
Hye Ri!

281
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,260
I'm busy. Don't call me at this hour from now on.

282
00:24:41,260 --> 00:24:43,500
Don't ever ask why.

283
00:24:47,370 --> 00:24:49,550
- The administrative office.
- Yeah.

284
00:24:51,260 --> 00:24:53,890
I wanted to live that life.

285
00:24:53,890 --> 00:24:58,660
Doing the work she might have done here.

286
00:24:58,660 --> 00:25:02,680
If I lived like her, who was truly happy,

287
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,020
could I be happy as well?

288
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:10,950
So did you become as happy as Hye Ri, Eun Ho?

289
00:25:10,950 --> 00:25:12,520
No.

290
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:17,560
I lived as her for three years,

291
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:22,900
but not at all.

292
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:26,770
Actually, Eun Ho...

293
00:25:26,770 --> 00:25:31,310
you came to see me many times as Hye Ri.

294
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:35,070
But the fact that you don't remember mean you have

295
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:39,100
Dissociative Identity Disorder.

296
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:47,540
Doctor, do you mean...

297
00:25:49,370 --> 00:25:52,780
I'm no longer pretending to be Hye Ri,

298
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:56,110
but I've really become her?

299
00:25:56,110 --> 00:26:00,080
Is that why I wrote that letter to myself when I was Hye Ri?

300
00:26:03,050 --> 00:26:06,120
Could I read the letter?

301
00:26:11,990 --> 00:26:15,730
Hello, Eun Ho. My name is Ju Hye Ri.

302
00:26:15,730 --> 00:26:18,820
I am your other identity.

303
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:23,320
I'm writing because I want to tell you something.

304
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:26,580
I found happiness,

305
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:29,140
and I don't want to let it go.

306
00:26:29,140 --> 00:26:31,570
Because...

307
00:26:31,570 --> 00:26:34,680
I have someone I love.

308
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:39,900
But in my dreams, you seemed really unhappy.

309
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:43,020
So I'm asking you,

310
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:48,480
even if you're the owner of this body,

311
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:53,250
please let me have it because I'm happy.

312
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:56,660
Please don't take me away from myself.

313
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:58,670
Because...

314
00:26:59,730 --> 00:27:04,220
I'm much happier than you are.

315
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:13,800
Look. You can see here

316
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:16,390
how you were as Hye Ri.

317
00:27:17,150 --> 00:27:20,770
When you first came to me, I recorded you with your consent.

318
00:27:20,770 --> 00:27:22,580
Let me see it.

319
00:27:24,390 --> 00:27:26,200
Are you sure?

320
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:29,000
Yes. I want to see it.

321
00:27:30,260 --> 00:27:34,940
Then what happens to me, Ju Hye Ri?

322
00:27:34,940 --> 00:27:37,540
Do I disappear?

323
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:39,780
Do I go away?

324
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:44,890
Eun Ho has only existed in my dreams.

325
00:27:44,890 --> 00:27:48,800
Doctor, I'm happy now.

326
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,110
I don't want to abandon Hye Ri.

327
00:27:51,110 --> 00:27:52,930
At least, in the present,

328
00:27:52,930 --> 00:27:57,540
I am much happier than Eun Ho from my dreams.

329
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:59,020
Doctor.

330
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:01,560
Yes, Eun Ho. Go ahead.

331
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:05,190
Did Ju Hye Ri seem...

332
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:10,920
happy to you, too?

333
00:28:27,470 --> 00:28:29,220
What did the doctor say?

334
00:28:32,300 --> 00:28:35,100
What? Is it serious?

335
00:28:37,930 --> 00:28:40,060
No.

336
00:28:40,060 --> 00:28:42,740
Wasn't that Shin Joong on the phone?

337
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:46,140
- Yeah.
- What did he say?

338
00:28:46,140 --> 00:28:48,200
Today is Department Head Oh's last day.

339
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:51,360
Really? I thought he was retiring at the end of the year.

340
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:55,290
Yeah, but it must have been decided last month.

341
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:59,910
So after the holiday, you'll be taking over the 9 o'clock news.

342
00:29:01,530 --> 00:29:02,840
Not sure.

343
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:05,090
What do you mean not sure?

344
00:29:05,970 --> 00:29:08,190
I think it's leaking.

345
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:11,750
This? I found it on the street.

346
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,270
Wait, for real?

347
00:29:13,270 --> 00:29:14,930
Would it be fake?

348
00:29:14,930 --> 00:29:17,920
Why did you have to pick up a broken one?

349
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:23,190
That's probably why it got thrown out. Then I found it.

350
00:29:23,190 --> 00:29:25,340
It wouldn't have been thrown out otherwise.

351
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:27,560
That seems logical.

352
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:05,100
Excuse me. Did Ju Hye Ri not come to work again?

353
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:09,430
No. She didn't.

354
00:30:09,430 --> 00:30:11,710
She usually does.

355
00:30:13,430 --> 00:30:15,390
Did she not come in yesterday, either?

356
00:30:16,190 --> 00:30:17,980
No.

357
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:20,360
You can't reach her, either?

358
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:23,450
No, I mean...

359
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:26,850
Ju Hye Ri doesn't have a phone.

360
00:30:28,570 --> 00:30:32,660
I thought so, too, but remember when she passed out in the restroom?

361
00:30:32,660 --> 00:30:35,680
At that time- hold on a second.

362
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:40,470
This was on the floor next to her.

363
00:30:42,100 --> 00:30:44,200
- It's a phone.
- Yes.

364
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:46,710
But it won't turn on, even after I charged it.

365
00:30:46,710 --> 00:30:48,990
I don't know whose this is.

366
00:30:48,990 --> 00:30:51,490
But I can't ask unless she's here.

367
00:30:51,490 --> 00:30:54,580
Hye Ri doesn't have a phone, and I don't have her address...

368
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:58,500
Can I bring that to her?

369
00:30:59,370 --> 00:31:01,940
I do know her address.

370
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,880
Sure. Of course.

371
00:31:14,460 --> 00:31:16,030
Thank you.

372
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:20,930
Excuse me!

373
00:31:24,580 --> 00:31:28,640
If you see Hye Ri, could you tell her something from me?

374
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,130
Like what?

375
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:33,920
That she's dead meat.

376
00:31:36,590 --> 00:31:37,930
Okay.

377
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:07,130
You hungry? Want me to make you something?

378
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:16,180
Are you hungry? Want me to make you something?

379
00:32:18,860 --> 00:32:20,040
Yes.

380
00:32:20,810 --> 00:32:23,050
I want something delicious.

381
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:26,110
Got it. I'll make you something delicious.

382
00:32:27,460 --> 00:32:30,350
Something high in calories.

383
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:32,120
Not that.

384
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:34,790
Do you know how puffy your face looks onscreen these days?

385
00:32:34,790 --> 00:32:37,370
Like you eat late at night every night.

386
00:32:40,430 --> 00:32:41,970
What's this?

387
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:48,500
Nothing.

388
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:50,260
Are you knitting these days?

389
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:52,410
You must have a lot of time on your hands.

390
00:32:52,410 --> 00:32:54,130
What? No.

391
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:56,770
So, what are you going to make me?

392
00:32:58,020 --> 00:33:00,380
Tomato and egg stir fry?

393
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:01,930
Wow.

394
00:33:01,930 --> 00:33:03,670
Sounds good.

395
00:33:28,030 --> 00:33:32,750
[Golden Holiday Special Live Broadcast]

396
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:37,090
Special live broadcast of "The Country Right Now, And Us" for the holiday weekend.

397
00:33:37,090 --> 00:33:40,870
Hello, we are at the Square Rest Stop.

398
00:33:40,870 --> 00:33:44,520
This is a place for people traveling for the weekend

399
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,240
to stop and rest for a while.

400
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:50,010
Yes. The rain that started at the top of the holiday weekend

401
00:33:50,010 --> 00:33:53,390
have subsided outside the Seoul region.

402
00:33:53,390 --> 00:33:56,590
Rain is planned to resume tomorrow morning,

403
00:33:56,590 --> 00:33:57,950
but right now,

404
00:33:57,950 --> 00:34:01,360
it's busy here with people enjoying the long weekend.

405
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:04,670
Should we chat with one of those people?

406
00:34:06,330 --> 00:34:08,450
Please call Yoo Ra.

407
00:34:09,470 --> 00:34:12,500
The main writer. Yoo Ra.

408
00:34:12,500 --> 00:34:14,320
Call her.

409
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:17,280
She's not picking up my calls.

410
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:19,570
Oh, well, that's...

411
00:34:19,570 --> 00:34:22,150
She did arrive here...

412
00:34:22,150 --> 00:34:27,160
I mean, she's not here. No, she wasn't able to...

413
00:34:27,160 --> 00:34:28,660
Then...

414
00:34:29,790 --> 00:34:32,170
could you deliver this message

415
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:35,730
to Yoo Ra what I'm about to say?

416
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:39,470
Yes. If you tell me, I can deliver the message...

417
00:34:39,470 --> 00:34:40,850
I was...

418
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,870
told I'd be the main emcee.

419
00:34:44,870 --> 00:34:48,390
But I didn't even get the first greeting.

420
00:34:48,390 --> 00:34:51,060
I keep being asked to do interviews,

421
00:34:51,060 --> 00:34:54,650
or to laugh at dumb jokes.

422
00:34:54,650 --> 00:34:56,170
That's...

423
00:34:57,290 --> 00:34:59,810
not how you do this.

424
00:34:59,810 --> 00:35:01,390
And her.

425
00:35:01,390 --> 00:35:03,280
That Baek Hye Yeon.

426
00:35:05,430 --> 00:35:08,220
I've been doing this for 15 years longer than her.

427
00:35:08,220 --> 00:35:12,410
But my role is smaller than hers.

428
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:18,080
What do you think will happen if you keep doing this?

429
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,290
Do you have a phone?

430
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:30,800
Unfortunately, I get no joy out of the selfishness of civilization.

431
00:35:46,510 --> 00:35:48,730
Sunbae, I'm scared.

432
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:51,570
That sunbae...

433
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:56,610
How should I say this? I think she might kill me.

434
00:35:56,610 --> 00:35:58,800
She wouldn't kill me, would she?

435
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:04,190
Or, Sunbae, I think that Sunbae might beat me up.

436
00:36:04,190 --> 00:36:09,150
Sunbae, I've been bullied a lot, but I've never been beaten up.

437
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:13,830
Am I going to get beaten up? It'd be my first time. I'm scared.

438
00:36:13,830 --> 00:36:17,080
Sunbae, is she always that scary?

439
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:19,170
You know...

440
00:36:19,170 --> 00:36:21,400
my heart is beating so fast.

441
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:25,600
But...

442
00:36:27,170 --> 00:36:30,630
how do you contact someone with a broken phone

443
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:34,130
or doesn't have one at all?

444
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:36,700
How would I know that?

445
00:36:42,140 --> 00:36:44,020
Hello.

446
00:36:44,020 --> 00:36:48,930
I'm looking for the contact information of an employee at the parking booth.

447
00:36:48,930 --> 00:36:50,550
Yes. Sure.

448
00:36:50,550 --> 00:36:52,520
I'm aware.

449
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:55,960
Are you crazy?

450
00:36:57,550 --> 00:37:00,530
I'm asking you. Are you crazy?

451
00:37:00,530 --> 00:37:03,210
- Well...
- What did you say when you called me a month ago?

452
00:37:03,210 --> 00:37:05,920
"Unni, we're doing a holiday special live broadcast.

453
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:09,130
We'll tour rest stops around the country, end up in Busan, and raise money.

454
00:37:09,130 --> 00:37:10,800
It's a very well-intentioned program.

455
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:15,900
Unni, I want you to be the main emcee on it.

456
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,680
What do you think, Unni?"

457
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:21,840
If we stand in line, does that make me the main emcee?

458
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:24,100
- It's not like that...
- Answer me, Yoo Ra.

459
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:26,760
Is that what you call a main emcee?

460
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:30,750
Because I don't think so. How do I say this?

461
00:37:30,750 --> 00:37:32,870
We might both be the main emcees,

462
00:37:32,870 --> 00:37:35,530
but Baek Hye Yeon is actually hosting.

463
00:37:35,530 --> 00:37:37,710
But what about me?

464
00:37:37,710 --> 00:37:41,400
I feel like I'm just being extra next to her.

465
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,830
Excuse me.

466
00:37:47,930 --> 00:37:49,380
- Me?
- Yes.

467
00:37:49,380 --> 00:37:51,730
Mi Rae says she won't do it.

468
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:56,400
- Do what?
- She says she won't host anymore.

469
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:59,490
She's so pissed about you that she won't do it.

470
00:37:59,490 --> 00:38:02,050
But as you know, we're toast without her.

471
00:38:02,050 --> 00:38:05,170
She says she'll skip all the rest stop footage from now on.

472
00:38:05,170 --> 00:38:08,330
Well, fine, I can deal with that.

473
00:38:08,330 --> 00:38:10,790
But if she misses filming tomorrow,

474
00:38:10,790 --> 00:38:13,740
we're completely toast.

475
00:38:15,310 --> 00:38:17,350
So I'm asking you.

476
00:38:18,130 --> 00:38:20,770
Please convince Mi Rae.

477
00:38:20,770 --> 00:38:23,000
I begged, but it didn't work.

478
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,500
Please help me out.

479
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:32,800
This is a special holiday live broadcast of "The Country Right Now, And Us."

480
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:35,350
We're at Mangjoong Rest Stop.

481
00:38:35,350 --> 00:38:39,660
We're much closer to the beaches of Busan.

482
00:38:39,660 --> 00:38:42,880
What's the weather like in Busan right now?

483
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:46,320
It's very clear in Busan.

484
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,260
Could you introduce yourself first?

485
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:51,360
Oh, yes. Me? I...

486
00:38:53,290 --> 00:38:55,450
We've met before.

487
00:38:55,450 --> 00:38:57,950
I've seen you before. For sure.

488
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,500
Yes.

489
00:39:01,500 --> 00:39:06,170
Hello. You don't need to go in person to experience Busan's weather.

490
00:39:06,170 --> 00:39:09,600
- Because the age we are living in...
- Damn it.

491
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:13,810
- has highly developed technology.
- Is he on Media N Seoul right now?

492
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:16,080
AI is changing our world...

493
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:20,830
- Did he get permission?
- But we are still living in an analog reality.

494
00:39:21,950 --> 00:39:25,340
Should I have gotten my makeup done?

495
00:39:30,190 --> 00:39:31,720
Excuse me.

496
00:39:33,050 --> 00:39:34,310
Me?

497
00:39:34,310 --> 00:39:35,650
Excuse me.

498
00:39:36,820 --> 00:39:38,730
You said you knew me earlier.

499
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:45,880
Of course, I do. I've seen you talking to Ju Eun Ho's sister.

500
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,300
Well...

501
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:50,330
who's Ju Eun Ho?

502
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:56,110
We'll gather in the lobby at 10 a.m. tomorrow and go to the studio together.

503
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:57,680
[Ju Eun Ho]
Got it!

504
00:39:57,680 --> 00:40:01,400
[Ju Eun Ho]
Great work! Thank you!

505
00:40:14,970 --> 00:40:17,300
Do you live with your family?

506
00:40:17,300 --> 00:40:19,360
No, I live alone.

507
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:22,420
I guess you can say I'm an only child.

508
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,730
Hey.

509
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:42,340
You know...

510
00:40:45,300 --> 00:40:48,700
I've done the 7 o'clock, 8 o'clock, and 9 o'clock news.

511
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:52,400
As in, I have as much, no...

512
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:55,880
more recognition than you.

513
00:40:55,900 --> 00:41:01,200
But do you know what that Press Director bastard called me and said?

514
00:41:02,730 --> 00:41:06,610
That I should be thankful to be on TV.

515
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:08,920
Why?

516
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,140
Because I'm old.

517
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:16,450
But everyone gets old.

518
00:41:16,450 --> 00:41:18,110
Including you.

519
00:41:19,090 --> 00:41:21,200
I'm saying...

520
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:27,300
you'll meet a hoobae like yourself and fuming just like me in a few years.

521
00:41:34,390 --> 00:41:36,400
I'm sorry,

522
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:41,100
but I have no intention of sharing a room with you.

523
00:41:42,870 --> 00:41:44,860
Excuse me, Sunbaenim.

524
00:41:46,650 --> 00:41:48,890
Why? What?

525
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:56,220
I won't share a room with you. I won't complain.

526
00:41:58,730 --> 00:42:02,240
But could you please do the broadcast tomorrow?

527
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:07,030
I'll ask the Press Director if we can split the lines.

528
00:42:09,970 --> 00:42:12,580
I beg you, Sunbaenim.

529
00:43:01,900 --> 00:43:03,780
Hey, it's me.

530
00:43:04,610 --> 00:43:06,280
Where are you?

531
00:43:07,860 --> 00:43:09,730
Can you maybe...

532
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,730
come here right now?

533
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:38,540
Do you usually not sleep?

534
00:43:38,540 --> 00:43:41,440
How can you sleep for 12 hours at a time?

535
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:45,270
Maybe you have a sleep disorder, not a panic disorder.

536
00:43:47,030 --> 00:43:50,290
Is it morning or not?

537
00:43:50,290 --> 00:43:53,100
Morning? It's evening.

538
00:43:56,180 --> 00:43:57,680
Well, I...

539
00:43:57,680 --> 00:43:59,710
What? What?

540
00:44:01,530 --> 00:44:04,900
Did I wake up at some point?

541
